The '''Terri Schiavo case''' was a [[court|legal battle]]. It involved prolonged [[life support]] in [[United States]]. The case began in 1998 and lasted to 2005. '''Teresa Marie "Terri" Schiavo''' was in [[Persistent Vegetative State]] and there was a [[controversy]] about stopping life support. She had collapsed in her [[St. Petersburg, Florida]] [[home]] because of [[cardiac arrest]] on February 25 1990. This had caused a large amount of [[damage]] to her [[brain]]. This damage caused her to be in a Persistent Vegetative State. Her feeding tube was disconnected March 18 2005. She died thirteen days later.

